Weather Forecast Prediction using Logistic Regression

This project focuses on predicting whether it will rain or not based on weather conditions using a Machine Learning classification model (Logistic Regression).

*Dataset Overview:
The dataset contains weather-related features such as:
Temperature
Humidity
Wind Speed
Cloud Cover
Pressure
Rain (Target Variable: Yes/No)

*Project Workflow:
1.Data Loading & Exploration
    Loaded dataset using Pandas
    Checked:
        Shape of data
        Data types and structure
        Statistical summary
    Identified:
        Missing values
        Duplicate records
2.Data Preprocessing
    Converted categorical target variable Rain (Yes/No) into numerical format (0/1) using Label Encoding
    Verified data cleanliness
3.Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
      Scatter Plot → Temperature vs Rain
      Correlation Heatmap → Relationship between features
      Histogram → Distribution of Temperature
    This helps understand:
        Feature relationships
        Data patterns
        Impact of variables on rainfall
4.Feature Selection
      Selected input features: Temperature, Humidity, Wind_Speed, Cloud_Cover, Pressure
      Target variable: Rain (0 = No, 1 = Yes)
5.Train-Test Split
      Split data into:
        70% Training
        30% Testing
        Used random_state=42 for reproducibility
6.Feature Scaling
      Applied StandardScaler to normalize data
      Important for Logistic Regression performance
7.Model Building
        Used Logistic Regression for binary classification
        Trained model on scaled training data
8.Model Evaluation
        Evaluated model using:
              Accuracy Score
              Confusion Matrix
              Classification Report
        These metrics help measure:
                    Prediction correctness
                    False positives & negatives
                    Precision, Recall, F1-score
*Results:
Model predicts whether it will rain based on weather conditions
Achieved good classification performance (Accuracy: 0.9266666666666666)
*Technologies Used:
      Python
      Pandas
      Matplotlib & Seaborn
      Scikit-learn
*Conclusion:
This project demonstrates how machine learning can be used for weather prediction by analyzing environmental factors and building a classification model.
